1 (a) The parent-child legal relationship may be
2 terminated if any one (1) or more of the following facts is
3 established by clear and convincing evidence:
4
5 (x) The child has been appointed a guardian who
6 is a relative of the child, the child has been under the
7 guardian's care for more than twenty-four (24) months and
8 the parent is unfit to have the custody and control of the
9 child.
10
11 Section 2. This act is effective July 1, 2025.
